[30;1m118 | [0m[35mool`[0m
[30;1m119 | [0m[35m        If a guild-specific command is not found when invoked, then try falling back into[0m
[30;1m120 | [0m[35m        a global command in the tree. For example, if the tree locally has a ``/ping`` command[0m
[30;1m121 | [0m[35m        under the global namespace but the guild has a guild-specific ``/ping``, instead of failing[0m
[30;1m122 | [0m[35m        to find the guild-specific ``/ping`` command it will fall back to the global ``/ping`` comma[0m
[30;1m123 | [0m[35m        This has the potential to raise more :exc:`~discord.app_commands.CommandSignatureMismatch` e[0m
[30;1m124 | [0m[35m        than usual. Defaults to ``True``.[0m
